### ðŸ§ª **Basic Git Workflow**

```bash
# Step 1: Initialize Git
git init

# Step 2: Create a file
echo "Hello Git" > file.txt

# Step 3: Check file status
git status

# Step 4: Add file to staging
git add file.txt

# Step 5: Commit the file
git commit -m "First commit"

# Step 6: Link with GitHub repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo-name.git

# Step 7: Push code to GitHub
git push -u origin main
```

---

### ðŸ§ª **Installing Git on AWS Linux Machines**

```bash
# Connect to EC2 instance
ssh -i "key.pem" ec2-user@<ip-address>

# Update packages
sudo yum update -y

# Install Git
sudo yum install git -y

# Verify installation
git --version
```

---

### ðŸ§ª **Add, Commit, Push, Pull & .gitignore**

```bash
# Step 1: Create a local repo
mkdir myrepo
cd myrepo
git init

# Step 2: Create and track files
touch file1.txt
nano file1.txt   # Add content & save
git status
git add file1.txt
git commit -m "First commit from Shaan"

# Step 3: View commit history
git log
git show <commit-id>

# Step 4: Push code to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/repo-name.git
git push -u origin master

# Step 5: Pull code from GitHub on another system
mkdir mypullrepo
cd mypullrepo
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/repo-name.git
git pull origin master

# Step 6: Edit & push again
nano file1.txt
git status
git add file1.txt
git commit -m "Second commit from Shaan"
git push origin master

# Step 7: Create .gitignore
touch .gitignore
nano .gitignore
# Example patterns:
*.log
temp.txt
mysecrets/

# Extra Commands
git log -1
git log -2
git log --oneline
git log --grep="fix"
```

---

### ðŸ§ª ** Branching, Merging, Stashing & Reset**

```bash
# Branch operations
git branch branch1
git branch
git checkout branch1
git checkout -b branch1
git branch

# Merge branch into master
git checkout master
git merge branch1

# Fix merge conflict manually if needed
git add filename
git commit -m "Resolved merge conflict"

# Stash operations
git stash
git stash list
git stash apply
git stash drop
git stash clear

# Reset operations
git reset --hard <commit-id>
git reset --hard HEAD~2

# Logs
git log --oneline
git log --grep="search-term"
```

---

### ðŸ§ª **â€“ Git Revert, Tags, Clone, and GitLab**

```bash
# Revert a commit
git revert <commit-id>

# Remove untracked files
git clean -n    # Preview
git clean -f    # Delete

# Tag commands
git tag <tagname> <commit-id>
git tag
git tag -d <tagname>

# Clone a repository
cd ~
mkdir myproject
cd myproject
git clone https://github.com/username/repo.git
cd repo

# Add and commit after cloning
touch file1.txt
nano file1.txt
git add file1.txt
git commit -m "Added file1"
git push origin main

# Log commands
git log -1
git log -2
git log --oneline
git log --grep="message"
```

